message.content: Sniper and trenchgun OP, *good combo

referenced_message.content:
<@254304862643159042> A few tips: Slide jumping is OP if you're using close range weapons. Make sure that you take advantage of the fact that there is (i'm pretty sure) no additional bloom/spread for shooting while moving. If you're up against AR and you're in close, make it as hard as possible for them to hit you. 

White AR is pretty strong and a lazor beam with basic attachments. Don't waste money on anything that doesn't reduce recoil though, besides maybe a red dot. Also start with red dot before you go to 2x imo. 

The trench gun ( white pump ) is pretty busted and can 2 shot most armors if you get close. Utilize cover to push them then your slide jump to gap close once you're close. Ez kills. 

Don't buy white sniper until your more comfortable, it's very good but it's expensive for a white weapon and not worth the cost if you're simply practicing.

edit_history.content: Sniper and trenchgun OP

message.content:
!suggest Honestly my main complaint here is the armor system and penetration system is not well done and just like everyone else I have my opinions about It. Personally I believe that armor should be a second health bar rather than just a percentile negation. Now before you start ranting that this is stupid and not apex just keep reading. Since penetration is already in it would instead just bypass a portion of the armor and instead hit your health bar directly but at a reduced amount. This would work the exact same way it already does except armor would be more effective against weapons that have lower pen.

Now you might say well this would give an unfair advantage to players who have better armor. Well simply make have a way to repair in game just like the stims we have now except they take longer and are much more difficult to use in the middle of a fight.

The goal of this would be to increase TTK for people who use good armor against people using budget guns. But you would still be able to take the same amount of hits from people with the same tier of guns. Pen mods and such or guns with an innately higher pen will just pen through the armor at a % amount and fights will feel pretty much the same.

Feedback:
1) I don't like the new medium zoom scopes. They block off more screen real estate for no real gain. If I wanted more peripheral vision, I'd just zoom out or use a secondary optic.
2) Anti-tank artillery is now the best artillery for killing infantry, and it's cheap. It's too good of a dual use option imo.
3) The new helo flight model is... interesting. I don't hate it given how cheap it is now; something had to balance that buff out. I don't mind it that much but I'm not sure if the downgrade was intentional.
4) The tank engine audio is much louder while you're in the tank now, which gets annoying. There should be an option to turn that volume down.
5) Not a fan of teamkill punish timeout. If someone wipes a whole friendly squad (which is happening more now) they should be put on a longer time out so they can think about what they did, which the old punish system allowed if people stacked their punishments.

edit_history.content:
Feedback:
1) I don't like the new medium zoom scopes. They block off more screen real estate for no real gain. If I wanted more peripheral vision, I'd just zoom out or use a secondary optic.
2) Anti-tank artillery is now the best artillery for killing infantry, and it's the cheapest. It's too good of a dual use option imo.
3) The new helo flight model is... interesting. I don't hate it given how cheap it is now; something had to balance that buff out. I don't mind it that much but I'm not sure if the downgrade was intentional.
4) The tank engine audio is much louder while you're in the tank now, which gets annoying. There should be an option to turn that volume down.
5) Not a fan of teamkill punish timeout. If someone wipes a whole friendly squad (which is happening more now) they should be put on a longer time out so they can think about what they did, which the old punish system allowed if people stacked their punishments.
